							</div><div class="video-title-wrapper">
											<div class="video-title"><h1>WHO Special Envoy: Coronavirus Will Stalk The Human Race For A Long Time, Until We Have A Vaccine</h1></div>
										</div>
										<div class="video-social">
						                    <div class="socialBar" data-print="1" data-style="short" data-dialog="share">
						                        <div class="left toolset"></div>
						                    </div>

						                    <div class="socialBar-clicks"> <span class="label"></span></div>
						           			<div class="socialBar-divide"> | </div>
						            		<div class="socialBar-shares"> <span class="label"></span></div>
						                </div>
						</div><!-- video-top --><div class="byline">
							 				Posted By <a href="https://www.realclearpolitics.com/authors/tim_hains">Tim Hains</a>
							 				<br/>On Date April 12, 2020
							 			</div>
							 			<br /><div class="body-photo-inline"><div class="rc_video_player_container"><center><iframe width="640" height="330" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_9RmsPh6Ggg" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe></center></div></div><!-- body-photo-inline --><div class="clear"></div><div class="video-body-text"><p>Sunday on NBC’s "Meet the Press," World Health Organization envoy David Nabarro warned that while the coronavirus may not be seasonal like normal influenza, it will "stalk the human race for quite a long time to come until we can all have a vaccine."<br />
<br />
"We're not so sure that it will come in waves in the way that influenza does," he said. "We think it is going to be a virus that stalks the human race for quite a long time to come until we can all have a vaccine that will protect us and that there will be small outbreaks that will emerge sporadically and they will break through our defenses."<br />
<br />
"The key in dealing with this virus is for every community to have a kind of defensive shield, to pick cases up as they appear, isolate them and stop outbreaks from developing."<br />
<br />
"It is going to be necessary for every single country to have that capacity. And so we’re actually encouraging countries to put that in place now, and that will facilitate releasing lockdowns and prevent further massive outbreaks."<p/><br /><br /><div class="video_p_ad"><div class="RC-AD RC-AD-BOX-MIDDLE"></div></div><p><p/></div><div class="breaking-related"><div class="label">Related Videos</div><div class="archive-item"><div class="archive-image-wrapper"><img src="https://assets.realclear.com/images/50/507085_2_.jpg" /></div><div class="archive-content-wrapper"><img src="/asset/img/camera-red.png" /><strong><a href='https://www.realclearpolitics.com/video/2020/04/12/cnns_jake_tapper_to_president_trump_what_is_the_plan_for_coronavirus.html' >CNN's Jake Tapper to President Trump: What Is The Plan For Coronavirus?</a></strong><span class='date'></span><div class="excerpt"><p>CNN's Jake Tapper asks the president if he has a plan to stop the spread of the novel coronavirus pandemic: "Attacking journalists who ask questions does not make those questions go away. It only reveals that you might not have the answers. Again, sir, respectfully, what is the plan for a way out...</p><div class='videos-related-tags'><ul class='tags'><li><a href='/stream/?topic=jake_tapper'>JAKE TAPPER</a></li><li><a href='/stream/?topic=coronavirus'>coronavirus</a></li></div></ul></div></div></div><div class="archive-item"><div class="archive-image-wrapper"><img src="https://assets.realclear.com/images/50/507086_2_.jpg" /></div><div class="archive-content-wrapper"><img src="/asset/img/camera-red.png" /><strong><a href='https://www.realclearpolitics.com/video/2020/04/12/nj_gov_murphy_were_fighting_to_stay_ahead_of_need_for_hospital_beds_ventilators_ppe.html' >NJ Gov. Murphy: "We're Fighting To Stay Ahead" Of Need For Hospital Beds, Ventilators, PPE</a></strong><span class='date'></span><div class="excerpt"><p>New Jersey Gov. Phil Murphy updated CNN Sunday morning about how New Jersey is grappling with the second-worst coronavirus outbreak of a state. 

"We're fighting to stay ahead on bed capacity, ventilators that are constantly running thin, the medicine you need for those ventilators, the personal...</p><div class='videos-related-tags'><ul class='tags'><li><a href='/stream/?topic=phil_murphy'>Phil Murphy</a></li><li><a href='/stream/?topic=coronavirus'>coronavirus</a></li></div></ul></div></div></div><div class="archive-item"><div class="archive-image-wrapper"><img src="https://assets.realclear.com/images/50/507087_2_.jpg" /></div><div class="archive-content-wrapper"><img src="/asset/img/camera-red.png" /><strong><a href='https://www.realclearpolitics.com/video/2020/04/12/chuck_todd_to_fda_commissioner_about_testing_failures_with_all_due_respect_what_went_wrong.html' >Chuck Todd to FDA Commissioner About Testing Failures: "With All Due Respect, What Went Wrong?"</a></strong><span class='date'></span><div class="excerpt"><p>NBC's "Meet the Press" host Chuck Todd interviews  FDA Commissioner Steve Hahn about why it took so long to get wide-scale testing for the coronavirus outbreak deployed nationwide. </p><div class='videos-related-tags'><ul class='tags'><li><a href='/stream/?topic=coronavirus'>coronavirus</a></li></div></ul></div></div></div></div><!--breaking-related--><div class="clear"></div><div class="no-widget"></div><div id="related-footer"><b>Related Topics: </b><a href="/stream/?topic=coronavirus">Coronavirus</a>, <a href="/stream/?topic=world_health_organization">World Health Organization</a></div><div class="comments-wrapper">
